body: Added minor optimizations for syncing all entities.
zip_safe is False in setup.py so that migrations work with other apps that use django entity
Entity uses newer celery package for Django and no longer depends on djcelery
Added EntityRelationship as an available model for the Entity API
The is_type filter returns True if there are no arguments
Renamed the cached_relationships function to cache_relationships
Updated API to change intersect_super_entities to has_super_entity_subset
Added additional filtering capabilities on django entity

name: 0.2.3 - Added jsonfield as a requirement
body: jsonfield was added as a requirement for django entity for proper installation

name: 0.2.2 - Turn on and off syncing entities
body:
This release adds the ability to turn on and off entity syncing

It also allows the user to run the sync_entities management command with an async option. async=True will use celery to sync entities

name: 0.2.1 - Added migrations
body: Added migrations to the project and to the setup file

name: 0.2 - Bug fixes for signals
body: This release fixes a bug that was causing the signal handlers to be called multiple times. This bug was fixed by adding a dispatch_uid field to the signal receiver definitions
Basic working version of django entity. Includes basic entity and entity relationship syncing
